Retro Code Library
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
This is a collection of extensions to the core Retro language.

Please see the individual files for copyright information and
license terms. (full license text can be found in the
'licenses' directory).
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
To use:

  1) Make sure the 'retro' binary is in your path
  2) Put a copy of the retroImage in the top-level directory
  3) Run ./libtool.sh to get a list of options
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Examples:

To enable support for prefixes, you will need to load the 'find'
and 'prefix' modules. The following will do this:

  ./libtool.sh --add contrib/find.retro contrib/prefix.retro

Your retroImage will now contain the find word and support for
prefixes. Specify the files in the order you wish to load them
in.

To learn about a module, use --info:

  ./libtool.sh --info contrib/find.retro

This will generally provide copyright, license, and some
descriptive text about the module.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
